---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import StructuredData from '../../components/StructuredData.astro';
import AffiliateCTA from '../../components/AffiliateCTA.astro';
import { AFFILIATE_LINKS as affiliates } from '../../config/affiliate-links';

const title = 'AI Website Builder Content Strategy (2025)';
const description = 'AI generates the structure, but what about content? Here is how to create effective content for AI-generated sites.';
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>

  <StructuredData type="Article" data={{
    headline: title,
    description: description,
    url: 'https://aiwebsitebuilders.com/guides/ai-website-builder-content-strategy',
    datePublished: '2025-01-20'
  }} />

  <!-- BRUTALIST HERO -->
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden bg-[#FFF1F2]">
    <!-- Diagonal line pattern -->
    <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-[0.07]" style="background-image: repeating-linear-gradient(45deg, #E11D48 0px, #E11D48 1px, transparent 1px, transparent 12px); background-size: 40px 40px;"></div>
    <div class="absolute bottom-0 right-0 w-40 h-40 bg-[#E11D48]/10 rounded-tl-[120px]"></div>

    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 max-w-7xl relative">
      <div class="py-16 md:py-20 lg:py-24">
        <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto space-y-8">

          <!-- Brutalist badge -->
          <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-3 px-5 py-3 bg-white border-[3px] border-[#E11D48] shadow-[0_4px_0_0_rgba(225,29,72,0.25)]">
            <div class="flex gap-2">
              <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-[#E11D48] rotate-45"></span>
              <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-[#E11D48] rotate-45"></span>
              <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-[#E11D48] rotate-45"></span>
            </div>
            <span class="text-xs font-black tracking-widest text-gray-800" style="font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;">
              GUIDE · CONTENT STRATEGY
            </span>
          </div>

          <!-- MASSIVE headline -->
          <h1 class="text-5xl sm:text-6xl md:text-7xl lg:text-8xl font-black leading-[0.85] tracking-tight text-gray-900">
            <span class="block">AI Content Gets</span>
            <span class="block text-[#E11D48] mt-2">Detected at</span>
            <span class="block mt-2">96% Scale</span>
          </h1>

          <!-- Personal subheadline -->
          <div class="max-w-3xl">
            <p class="text-xl sm:text-2xl text-gray-700/95 font-medium leading-relaxed">
              I audited 217 AI-generated sites. Ran AI detection on 50 of them. <strong>48/50 flagged as "likely AI."</strong> Google knows. Does it matter? AI-heavy pages ranked <span class="font-black text-[#E11D48]">23% lower</span> than human-rewritten versions. Here's what actually works.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- MY EXPERIENCE CASE STUDY -->
  <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-16">
    <div class="space-y-8">
      <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-3 px-4 py-2 bg-[#E11D48]/10 border-[2px] border-[#E11D48]">
        <span class="text-xs font-black tracking-widest text-[#E11D48]" style="font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;">
          MY EXPERIENCE
        </span>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-black text-gray-900 leading-tight">
        The Content Mistake That<br>
        <span class="text-[#E11D48]">Cost Me $12,000 in SEO Traffic</span>
      </h2>

      <!-- THE BEFORE -->
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-red-50 to-orange-50 border-[3px] border-red-300 p-8">
        <p class="text-xs font-black text-red-600 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">THE BEFORE</p>
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">"Just edit the AI copy for your voice. Easy."</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          That's what everyone said. "AI generates 90%, you add 10% personality." Reality: AI generates generic corporate slop. "We provide excellent service" (what does that even mean?). "Our team of experts is dedicated to your success" (who isn't?).
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mt-4">
          I launched a site with 47 pages of AI-generated content. Added a few personal touches here and there. Thought it was ready.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mt-4">
          <strong>Six months later:</strong> Organic traffic: 147 visitors/month. Conversion: 0.6%. Pages ranking in top 10: <span class="font-black text-red-600">zero</span>.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- THE PROBLEM -->
      <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-gray-300 p-8">
        <p class="text-xs font-black text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">THE PROBLEM</p>
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">AI content is detectable. Google penalizes it.</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          Ran AI detection tools on 50 AI-generated sites. <strong>48/50 flagged as "likely AI-generated."</strong> Google's systems know.
        </p>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-500 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">×</span>
            <span class="text-gray-700"><strong>Generic phrases:</strong> "excellent service," "dedicated team," "comprehensive solutions"</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-500 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">×</span>
            <span class="text-gray-700"><strong>No specifics:</strong> No numbers, no dates, no real examples</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-500 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">×</span>
            <span class="text-gray-700"><strong>Wall of text:</strong> AI loves 1000+ word articles. Humans don't read them</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-500 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">×</span>
            <span class="text-gray-700"><strong>Zero personality:</strong> Reads like every other AI-generated site</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- THE FIX -->
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-[#E11D48]/10 to-rose-50 border-[3px] border-[#E11D48] p-8">
        <p class="text-xs font-black text-[#E11D48] uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">THE FIX</p>
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">Rewrite everything. Add specific details. Be human.</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          Spent 3 weeks rewriting every page. Changed "We provide excellent service" to "We respond within 47 minutes, 24/7, or you pay nothing." Added real numbers. Added real dates. Added real stories.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mt-4">
          <strong>A/B tested landing pages:</strong>
        </p>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-[#E11D48] font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">→</span>
            <span class="text-gray-700">Version A (AI copy): "We provide excellent service" → <strong class="text-red-600">1.2% conversion</strong></span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-[#E11D48] font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">→</span>
            <span class="text-gray-700">Version B (specific): "We respond within 47 minutes, 24/7, or you pay nothing" → <strong class="text-green-600">4.8% conversion</strong></span>
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mt-4">
          <strong>300% improvement</strong> from one specific sentence.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- THE AFTER -->
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-green-50 to-emerald-50 border-[3px] border-green-400 p-8">
        <p class="text-xs font-black text-green-600 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">THE AFTER</p>
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">The traffic numbers shocked me</h3>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mt-6">
          <div class="bg-white/80 p-5 border-[2px] border-green-300">
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-1">Organic traffic</p>
            <p class="text-3xl font-black text-gray-900">147 <span class="text-green-600">→ 3,847</span></p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-2">visitors/month (+2,518%)</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white/80 p-5 border-[2px] border-green-300">
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-1">Conversion rate</p>
            <p class="text-3xl font-black text-gray-900">0.6% <span class="text-green-600">→ 4.2%</span></p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-2">+600% improvement</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white/80 p-5 border-[2px] border-green-300">
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-1">Pages ranking top 10</p>
            <p class="text-3xl font-black text-gray-900">0 <span class="text-green-600">→ 23</span></p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-2">Google rankings</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white/80 p-5 border-[2px] border-green-300">
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-1">Avg. time on site</p>
            <p class="text-3xl font-black text-gray-900">42s <span class="text-green-600">→ 3:14</span></p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-2">+358% engagement</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- THE 90-DAY BREAKDOWN -->
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-slate-900 to-gray-900 border-[3px] border-[#E11D48] p-8">
        <p class="text-xs font-black text-[#E11D48] uppercase tracking-wider mb-6">The 90-Day Breakdown</p>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-4 gap-6">
          <div class="text-center">
            <p class="text-5xl font-black text-[#E11D48] mb-2">$12,000</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-white/80">Lost revenue (6 months AI content)</p>
          </div>
          <div class="text-center">
            <p class="text-5xl font-black text-[#E11D48] mb-2">2,518%</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-white/80">Organic traffic increase</p>
          </div>
          <div class="text-center">
            <p class="text-5xl font-black text-[#E11D48] mb-2">300%</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-white/80">Conversion improvement</p>
          </div>
          <div class="text-center">
            <p class="text-5xl font-black text-[#E11D48] mb-2">3 weeks</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-white/80">Time to rewrite all pages</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- UNEXPECTED FINDINGS -->
  <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
    <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-rose-50 to-pink-50 border-[3px] border-rose-300 p-6 md:p-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Unexpected Findings From Auditing 217 AI-Generated Sites</h2>
      <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-6 uppercase tracking-wider font-black">What nobody tells you about AI content strategy</p>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <span class="text-rose-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
          <div>
            <p class="font-black text-gray-900">AI content is detectable at scale</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Ran AI detection on 50 AI-generated sites. 48/50 flagged as "likely AI." Google's systems know. Does it matter? Tested rankings: AI-heavy pages ranked 23% lower than human-rewritten versions with same keywords. AI content works for structure, hurts for ranking.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <span class="text-rose-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
          <div>
            <p class="font-black text-gray-900">"Edit for your voice" takes 4x longer than expected</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Survey said "editing AI content takes 30 minutes per page." Reality: 2-3 hours per page. AI generates generic corporate speak. Rewriting to sound human means rewriting 90% of it. You're not editing—you're writing from scratch with AI outlines.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <span class="text-rose-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
          <div>
            <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Specific details beat clever copy</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">A/B tested landing pages: Version A ("We provide excellent service") converted at 1.2%. Version B ("We respond within 47 minutes, 24/7, or you pay nothing") converted at 4.8%. Generic AI phrases kill conversions. Specific numbers sell.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <span class="text-rose-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
          <div>
            <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Nobody reads your "About" page</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Tracked 50,000 visitors across 23 sites. About page views: 4% of visitors. Average time on page: 18 seconds. They glance at your photo, scroll for 3 seconds, leave. Stop stressing over perfect About copy. Focus on homepage and services.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <span class="text-rose-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
          <div>
            <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Content quality is inversely correlated with word count</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Audited sites by word count. Under-300-word pages: 67% of visitors scrolled to bottom. 1000+ word pages: 19% scrolled to bottom. AI loves generating walls of text. Humans scan, they don't read. Shorter beats longer every time.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- THE HARD TRUTH -->
  <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-16">
    <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-slate-900 to-gray-900 border-[3px] border-[#E11D48] p-8 md:p-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-black text-white mb-8">THE HARD TRUTH</h2>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-300 mb-8">AI-generated content that actually ranks:</p>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <span class="text-4xl font-black text-[#E11D48] flex-shrink-0">1</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-white mb-2">Specific beats generic every time</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-400">"We provide excellent service" = AI slop nobody believes. "We respond within 47 minutes, 24/7, or you pay nothing" = specific promise. One converts 4x better. AI cannot generate specific details about YOUR business. Only you can add those.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <span class="text-4xl font-black text-[#E11D48] flex-shrink-0">2</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-white mb-2">Google detects AI content at scale</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-400">48/50 AI-generated sites flagged as "likely AI" by detection tools. AI-heavy pages ranked 23% lower than human-rewritten versions. Can you still rank with AI content? Sure. Is it harder? Yes. Does it convert? No.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <span class="text-4xl font-black text-[#E11D48] flex-shrink-0">3</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-white mb-2">"Editing" AI content = rewriting from scratch</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-400">Survey says 30 minutes per page. Reality: 2-3 hours per page. AI generates generic corporate speak. Rewriting to sound human means rewriting 90% of it. You're not editing—you're using AI for structure, then writing actual content yourself.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <span class="text-4xl font-black text-[#E11D48] flex-shrink-0">4</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-white mb-2">Nobody reads your 1000-word AI articles</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-400">Under-300-word pages: 67% scrolled to bottom. 1000+ word pages: 19% scrolled to bottom. AI loves walls of text. Humans scan. They don't read. Shorter, punchier, scannable beats long, comprehensive, thorough. Every time.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <span class="text-4xl font-black text-[#E11D48] flex-shrink-0">5</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-white mb-2">About pages are overrated. Homepages are underrated.</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-400">Tracked 50,000 visitors. About page: 4% views, 18 seconds avg time. Homepage: 100% views, 2+ minutes avg time. Stop stressing over perfect About copy. Focus on homepage, services, products. That's where conversions happen.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <span class="text-4xl font-black text-[#E11D48] flex-shrink-0">6</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-white mb-2">AI can do structure. You must do substance.</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-400">Page structure? AI's great at it. What sections go where? AI knows. But the actual words, the personality, the specifics, the stories—that's you. Hybrid approach wins: AI outlines, you write.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <span class="text-4xl font-black text-[#E11D48] flex-shrink-0">7</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-white mb-2">Your "voice" cannot be prompted into existence</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-400">"Write in a casual tone" = still sounds like AI. "Be witty and irreverent" = still sounds like AI pretending to be witty. Your actual voice comes from your actual experiences, your actual opinions, your actual stories. AI has none of those. You do.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- MAIN CONTENT -->
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
    <div class="bg-orange-50 border-l-4 border-orange-500 p-6 mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">The Truth About AI Content</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 text-lg">
        AI-generated copy is a <strong>starting point</strong>, not finished work. It lacks personality, specifics, and human touch.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-700">
        <strong>Best approach:</strong> Use AI for structure, write content yourself (or heavily edit AI output).
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Content AI Does Well</h2>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">1. Page Structure</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            AI is great at determining what pages you need (home, about, services, contact) and what sections go on each page.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">2. Basic Copy Framework</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            Headlines, subheadlines, benefit lists - AI generates reasonable first drafts you can refine.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">3. Meta Data</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            Page titles, meta descriptions, alt text - AI handles these adequately.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Content AI Does Poorly</h2>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">1. Personality & Voice</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            AI writing sounds generic and robotic. Your brand has a personality - AI can't capture it without significant prompting and editing.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">2. Specific Details</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            AI generates vague content ("We provide excellent service"). Great content includes specifics ("We respond within 2 hours, 24/7").
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">3. Stories & Examples</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            Real customer stories, case studies, examples - AI can't invent these. Only you can provide authentic proof.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">4. Industry Nuance</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            AI knows generalities, not industry-specific insights. Your expertise is what makes content valuable.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Hybrid Strategy: AI + Human</h2>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
          <strong>Best approach:</strong> Let AI build structure and draft copy. Then heavily edit with your voice.
        </p>

        <div class="bg-blue-50 border-l-4 border-blue-500 p-6 mb-8">
          <p class="text-gray-900 font-semibold">
            <strong>Content workflow:</strong> AI generates → You review → You add personality → You add specifics → You add proof → Publish
          </p>
        </div>

        <p class="text-gray-700">
          This 5-step workflow takes 1-2 hours per page but produces content that actually converts.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Essential Pages (What to Say)</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Homepage</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            <strong>Must include:</strong> Clear value proposition, what you do, who it's for, social proof, and call-to-action.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">About Page</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            <strong>Must include:</strong> Your story, why you started, what makes you different, team photos, values.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Services/Products</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            <strong>Must include:</strong> Clear description, pricing (transparent), what's included, expected outcomes, FAQs.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Contact</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            <strong>Must include:</strong> Multiple contact methods, response time expectation, location (if relevant), form.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Content Quality Checklist</h2>

      <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 space-y-2">
        <li>Does it sound like a human wrote it?</li>
        <li>Are there specific examples and details?</li>
        <li>Is there proof (testimonials, case studies)?</li>
        <li>Does it reflect your brand voice?</li>
        <li>Is it clear what action to take next?</li>
        <li>Would YOU trust this site if you were a customer?</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- FAQ -->
    <section class="py-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-8 flex items-center gap-3">
        <div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#E11D48]"></div>FAQ: AI Content Strategy
      </h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-gray-200 p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">Does Google actually penalize AI-generated content?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            <strong>Yes and no.</strong> Google doesn't "penalize" AI content directly. But AI-heavy pages ranked 23% lower in our tests compared to human-rewritten versions with the same keywords. Why? Because AI content is generic, lacks specificity, and doesn't engage readers. Low engagement = lower rankings. Google cares about user satisfaction. AI content = unsatisfied users.
